{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696398/1930111401/0729.xml":{"full_text":"4\n\u25a0STRICT TRUDE\nSfiTISFAGTDRY\nBusiness conditions in the Dis\ntrict of Columbia are \u201cfairly\n\u25a0satisfactory,\u201d with indications\n\u25a0that industry will improve within\n\u25a0the next month, according to a\n\u25a0survey published today in the\n\u25a0current issue of the Industrial\n\u25a0Employment Bulletin, published\n\u25a0tn this city.\nThe Bulletin carries reports\n\u25a0from every State, and shows con\n\u25a0ditions here to be better than\n\u25a0the average. It says that the\n\u25a0majority of Industrial establish\n\u25a0ments here, during the month of\n\u25a0October, operated on fairly satis\n\u25a0factory production schedules with\n\u25a0their usual forces employed in\n\u25a0most instances. However, it adds,\n\u25a0a surplus of labor prevailed\n\u25a0throughout the month, including\nbuilding tradesmen, salespersons,\n\u25a0white and colored domestic help\n\u25a0and unskilled workers.\nThe survey continues:\n\u201cThe volume of public utility\nI work under way in the pant 30\ndays exceeded that of the\nprevious month, with prospects\nI for a further increase during\n/B November. The hotels and\ns Stores expect to Increase their\nforces during the next few\nweeks in preparation for the\nholiday trade. The 1930 street-\nImprovement program was near\nfl ing completion toward the close\ne I of the month.\n\u201cQuite a number of men that\nI have been employed in this\nwork will be retained through-\nout the winter on a five-day-\nI week basis, instead of being re-\nleased as in the past winter\nperiods. Federal and private\nI building projects continued to\noffer employment to large num-\nI bers of unskilled laborers.\u201d\nto Hear\nI [Australian Lecture\nThe Biological Society meets\ntomorrow at 8 p. m. in the new\nassembly hall of the Cosmos J\nClub, W. H. White, correspond-\nI Ing secretary, announced today.\nA lecture with motion pictures\nand slides, on the natural history\nlof the barrier reef of Australia,\nwill be given by Melbourne Ward,\nof the Australian Museum.\nI F. G. Ashbrook, Biological Sur-\nI vey, will show motion pictures of\nthe fur industry of the United\nStates.\nI Blonde Acquitted in\nBlack Mate's Death\nBALLSTON SPA. N. Y., Nov.\n14 (1.NJ3.). \u2014A pretty 26-year-old\nblonde, Mrs. Helen Abernathy,\nformerly of Chicago, today stood\nI acquitted of the murder of her\npegro husband, William Aber\n\u25a0wbthy, who was shot and killed\nB l fa Saratoga Springs in August.\nThe girl, on the stand in her\nown defense, said she married\nI Abernathy when she was out of\nig\u00df her head, and that when she at-\ntempted to leave him he grappled\nI with her and, in the struggle, a\ngun was discharged, sending a\nbullet into his heart.\nJulius Lansburgh Furniture Co., Entrance 909 F St.\nFOUR OUTSTANDING RADIOS\nNationally Advertised Standard Radios at Nationally Advertised Prices,\nWith No Extra or Carrying Charge for Convenient Deferred Payments\nATWATER KENT R. C. A. RADIOLA\nLOW-BOY hi-boy \u25a0IBmI\nI Th J io Wi lh tht \u201cSuperheterodyne\" HlHlsSrol\nGolden Voice\u201d MHWpQOPvBffI\n\u25a0M *ll9 *l42 50 Htm\nw i II Bk-tj\nW f This exquisite radio is incased The tasteful console cabinet\nin the finest of cabinets. New will immediately win your ap-\nand vast improvements have been ol {4 n w\neffected. A true quality radio. pro and lts P erf rmance Jour\nu praise.\nPHILCO CONSOLE MAJESTIC\nBABY GRAND LOW-BOY\njl M \u201cBalanced Unit.\" \u201cMighty Monarch of the Air\" II\n5 69 50 H 26 BpMI\nF Full-fledged performing Philco The new Majestic closely ap-\nHR X t__Ji-J ia this dainty Baby Grand 7-tube Proaches the ultimate possible in OUL HA-\nconsole radio. The darling of the Inclosed in exquisitely finished\nday. i cabinet.\n$lO Delivers Any of These Standard Radios\nl 1\n(Julius Xansburgh Jurniture\njggg^^^^gggggS\u00dfgggggg^Entrance\u2014 9o9 F St. N.\nHarvester Co. to Give\nJitaff, Ex-Workers\nLoan Relief\nCHICAGO, Nov. 14 (INJ3.).\nInternational Harvester Com\npany, leading manufacturer of\nagricultural implements, today\nannounced a plan to help guide\nits employes and former em\nployes over the present business\ndepression.\nUnder this plan the com\npany announced that it is pre\npared to take care on the actual\nliving requirements of employes\nwho have been laid off by ad\nvancing moderate loans if they\nare unable to procure tempo\nrary work.\no those who own stock in\nthe company loans will be made\nby the company or through\nbanks. Where the employes\nhave no resources moderate\nloans will be advanced on the\nagreement that they be repaid\nover a comfortable period,\nofficers of the company an\nnounced.\n1 LaNSBURCH'S\njy'T 7th, Bth and E Sts.\u2014NAtional 9800\nC'~ Connection With Any Other Washington Store\nJ \u201cIt's Inexpensive To Be Fash-\nona W e When Y\u00b0 u Wear This\nEvening Dress\nWith a Rhinestone\nStudded Peplum\nmm 74\nBewitching... irresistible... why hesi-\nffl\u00dfflfllH tate, it\u2019s only $9.74, but it looks like\nfIIHBIHI much, much more. Dull crepe, of\n/JlNllfl course in black, green or flesh. Sizes\nbMbMI 14 to 20\n/\u25a0BbiIIIIII Fur Trimmed Coats are\nSmart, But only $23.74\na 9 I Copies of the season\u2019s most successful coat\nfashions! Black and green. Fashioned for\n|VT youth! 14 to 20.\nINEXPENSIVE SHOP\u2014SECOND FLOOR\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\nTHREAT IS SENT\nTO POLICEMAN\nCHICAGO, Nov./ 14 (INS.).\nPoliceman Joseph Keating, the\nsecond State\u2019s witness in the mur\nder case against William \"Three-\nFingered Jack\u201d White to be\nmarked for death, was under\nguard today following a death\nwarning.\nKeating reported to State\u2019s\nattorney\u2019s prosecutors that he\nhad been sent the brief message:\n\u201cKeating is next.\u201d The police\nman was assigned to gather evi\ndence against Whitey a reputed\nracketeer with Capone affilia\ntions. Working with him was\nSergt. James Mc\u00dfride, who was\nshot and seriously wounded on\na street car in an attempt on\nthe part of the gang to prevent\nhis appearance in court.\nSince the attack on Mc\u00dfride,\nKeating has been acting as one\nof his bodyguards.\nIndian\u2019s Talk Flayed\nBy Head of D. C.\nHebrews\nCharacterizing the talk given\nat the Temple of the Congre\ngation by Syud Hossain, Na\ntionalist leader of India, as\nintemperate and a \u201cKross viola\ntion of courtesy\u201d Joseph Salo\nman, president of the Washing\nton Hebrew Congregation has\nformally expressed his resent\nment.\nThe Indian speaker, accord\ning to the understanding of\nthe leaders of the Hebrew\nCongregation, was to have\nspoken on \u201cNon-Violence as\nTaught by the Great Prophets.\u201d\nInstead he \"flayed the Chris\ntian religion as an entirety,\nits leaders in particular, and a\ngovernment (Great Britain)\nwith which this country is on\nmost friendly relations,\u201d assert\ning the Christianity was re\nsponsible for the World War.\nThe National Dally\nLINCOLN PARK CITIZENS\nThe monthly meeting of the\nLoncoln Park Citizens Association\nwill be held Monday, at 8 p. m.,\nMaker Had 100 Winter Coat*\nLike Tho\u00bbe We Sell Regularly at $22.50\n_A It Waa Time to Start Spring Cutting\n\u25a0F el I So He Sold Them to Us at a Low!\ngSF-Jk 10\u00b0 WINTER COATS\nLaden wfth Lovely'Furs\nDuplicates of /fe 4 O F7 F*\nOar Regular <R \u00a3g.\n$22.50 Coats!\nHere\u2019s a golden opportunity to save! If you\nwish to economize on your Winter coat\ncome tomorrow! If you would like to save\nenough on a coat to buy accessories\u2014come\ntomorrow! These are coats identical in\nevery way with our $22.50 models \u2014m\nbroadcloth, in lining, in fur trimming!\nBlack, brown and green\nSize* 14 to 20\na nd 36 to 44 med Y nth nlk m match\nmg color\n.Interlined for warmth\nStraightline and fitted\nmodels\nVicuna, lapin (rabbit)\ncuffs\nComplete selection for\nChildren\u2019s Warm misses and women\nFleece\nUNION SUITS\n2 A>r\nKeep the 